idk how to describe how i'm feeling really. i'm starting to get really stressed about money, which is my own fault. i should quit spending my money on shit(like weed and food). cuz i have 625 a month in rent, prob bout 75 for phone a month, 58 for Pclub, and i still have a $300 doctor bill to pay. i've been getting fewer hours at the dog haus (which is my own fault) and fewer hours at culvers, which if heidi doesn't give me the raise she told me i was getting 3 months ago soon then i'm gonna be a done one at the cut because frankly fuck that place aside from most of the people that work there. but all that plays back into where else can i find a job and i still want to go back to school so idk what i'd do for work when i go to school. And i know my expenses aren't all that high compared to some people and i'm getting a deal with rent and shit, but for how much i make it's enough to make me stress cuz i don't wanna lose what i have and become homeless.
 Then i have this feeling that idk anyone anymore, or that i've just lost touch with just the world. and again i can only blame myself, but it just seems that there isn't enough time for all the shit i wanna do and get done. i work most of the day, then want to relax or am too tired and i never have the same schedule so that always jumps around. i just feel very lost in a way. i know me atleast i just feel i'm wasting away, and i really hate stressing about money. i want more of it because i want to mainly finish with the tattoos i started and just get more. tattoos really mellow me out and allow me to deal with all the bullshit that life and people throws at you. With each new tattoo i get i feel more energized, happier and full of life. i find my body more beautiful covered with ink then the plain ol skin. Another reason i really want to go back to school, or i guess i should say just go to college, is because since i was hella slackin' at east and did night school and graduated. I feel i'm progessively getting dumber and dumber. like my memory is getting worse and i'm just forgetting things. and don't anyone blame it on the amount of weed i smoke, i had horrible learning and memory issues before that came. i feel also my vocab is slipping and words before tha ti knew how to spell i don't anymore. i just want to stimulate my mind and keep myself thinking and busy. actually make a difference in the world instead of sleeping or dicking around.
  But then with the whole school issue, i don't really know what i want to do. I have such a strong passion for animals and i want to work with them. i just dunno what would be a good fit. Especially with the failing economy i want to go into something that does pay well, but that i also enjoy doing and don't dread going to. well i love going to the dog haus but i can't work there my whole life nor can it really pay the bills. I keep second guessing myself and judging my capabilities from how i was in high school. even not in school i'd liike to think i'm more focused and determined but i'm just so worried that my previous problems of not giving a damn or hating homework or the fact that i will forget something i just learned super quick and then be lost. people have said well just don't do a full load take longer. i can't do that because if i'm not going into it with full force then i might as well not do it because i won't care as much, then it'll take longer and i'll be in school longer which is no fun or i won't take it as seriously. and theres also my view of my "love-life" but i cna't get into that because it'll seem even more of a cluster fuck than this already has. 
 I often feel that everyday is a struggle for me to just not give up. to keep trying. i know i need outside help but idk how to find the time to get it and still be able to afford bills and everything. my emotions can change in the blink of an eye. i can't always control my anger and i feel unhappy a lot. i know my life isn't super bad or anything. I'm grateful for a lot i have and the people who have been there for me. but i just don't feel happy. only when i'm getting tattooed/thinking of tattoo ideas or when i'm with natalie is when i really do or when i smoke weed(which if there's someone who reads this and doesn't like it then suck it. it's my life and my body, i can do what i want whether it's illegal or not. and if you want to form some sort of negative opinion of me because of this choice of mine then suck it again. it doesn't make me any different of a person, if anything i'm more open minded and less quick to dismiss and write things off since i've started. and i know how to separate work from play. work first play second). and of course some days are better than others where i'll just be in a better mood and chipper. im sure my eating, sleeping and exercise habits play a role in it all, which i'm trying to work on but is easier said than done sometimes....Going back to the school thing. i've also been finding it harder and harder to convey how i feel about something or how something impacts me. like with some things(animals, the love i have for my family, how a certain bands' music makes me feel, the person i love, etc. etc.)the emotions that are brought on by them or have for them are just so intense i suppose i'd say that i just feel i have to explain why i feel that way and which certain aspects make me feel that way and i just want to explain and describe every nook and cranny of said thing that it sometimes overwhelms me. i feel or hope that with more school, i can expand my vocab and thought processes to better articulate my words so that i can make people understand. and maybe so i can understand myself. who knows really. it's all weird. Life'll work itself out in due time. 
  I must also add that i feel a lot better after writing this. i've been meaning to try and do something in depth. i feel that i've gotten a bit off my chest. take it or leave it this is what came out.

p.s.-i did not go back through and edit this or anything, so there are plenty of spelling errors and jumping around and repeats of statements but oh well. deal

So...just got done watching Dragonball evolution courtesy of our bootleg masters from the far east and it was probably the worst thing ever. first thing that pissed me off is that Goku is a teenager living with his grandpa gohan. second he's in high school. third he's bullied at school and his nickname is geekoo. fourth he trains with master roshi for a quick second. alright fucking the numbering of them. the only characters included were goku, grandpa gohan, master roshi, bulma, chi chi and yamcha. and yamcha didn't even fight goku at all, he just trapped them in a hole and tried to get money out of em. no red ribbon army or emperor pilaf. wtf is this bullshit. master roshi is killed and brought back using the dragonballs and it only takes one kamehameha to defeat piccolo. i would recommend seeing it just to see how horrible it is. and there's supposed to be 2 more bullshit movies like this.

National Day of Slayer
6.6.06 isn't a date that comes around very often (once per century, to be exact), and while plenty of stupid horror movies and terrible albums will be released for the hype value of the day that bears "the number of the beast", we here at NDoS decided that this would be a perfect day for Hessians across the country to come together and engage in something upon which we can all agree - listening to Slayer! Also, do you really want those evangelical Neo-Cons to have all the fun with their "National Day of Prayer"?

Official Statement on Participation
----------
Listen to Slayer at full blast in your car.
Listen to Slayer at full blast in your home.
Listen to Slayer at full blast at your place of employment.
Listen to Slayer at full blast in any public place you prefer.
DO NOT use headphones! The objective of this day is for everyone within earshot to understand that it is the National Day of Slayer. National holidays in America aren't just about celebrating; they're about forcing it upon non-participants.


Taking that participation to a problematic level
-----------
Stage a "Slay-out." Don't go to work. Listen to Slayer.
Have a huge block party that clogs up a street in your neighborhood. Blast Slayer albums all evening. Get police cruisers and helicopters on the scene. Finish with a full-scale riot.
Spray paint Slayer logos on churches, synagogues, or cemeteries.
Play Slayer covers with your own band (since 99% of your riffs are stolen from Slayer anyway).
Kill the neighbor's dog and blame it on Slayer.

I remember growing up like it was only yesterday
Mom & Daddy tried their best to guide me on my way
But the hard times & the liquor drove the easy love away
And the only love I knew about was hard love

It was hard love, every hour of the day
When Christmas to my birthday was a million years away
And the fear that came between them drove the tears into my play
There was love in daddy's house, but it was hard love

And I recall the gentle courtesy you gave me as I tried
To dissemble in politeness all the love I felt inside
And for every song of laughter was another song that cried
This ain't no easy weekend, this is hard love

It was hard love, every step of the way
Hard to be so close to you, so hard to turn away
And when all the stars and sentimental songs dissolved to day
There was nothing left to sing about but hard love

So I loved you for your courage, and your gentle sense of shame
And I loved you for your laughter and your language and your name
And I knew it was impossible, but I loved you just the same
Though' the only love I gave to you was hard love

It was hard love, it was hard on you, I know
When the only love I gave to you was love I couldn't show
You forgave the heart that loved you as your lover turned to go
Leaving nothing but the memory of hard love

So I'm standing in this phone booth with a dollar and a dime
Wondering what to say to you to ease your troubled mind
For the Lord's cross might redeem us, but our own just wastes our time
And to tell the two apart is always hard, love

So I'll tell you that I love you even though I'm far away
And I'll tell you how you change me as I live from day to day
How you help me to accept myself and I won't forget to say
Love is never wasted, even when it's hard love

Yes, it's hard love, but it's love all the same
Not the stuff of fantasy, but more than just a game
And the only kind of miracle that's worthy of the name
For the love that heals our lives is mostly hard love

hey all who read this, i was wondering what your views on downloading music/filesharing are. 

so many people have bitched about how it's stealing money from the artists, but i think in some ways it opens up oppurtunities for them to make more. now i'll go in to why i think this. yes it does make them lose some money, but if you think about it, a lot of bands have more then one cd and also release merchandise such as shirts, stickers, patches and hoodies. now when someone downloads a cd without paying for it, the artist doesn't get the money from the cd, but if the person downloading the cd really likes the band and are really into music, as are many people nowadays, they will be more inclined to buy the other cds they can't download, and even the merchandise, which generates money for the artists. and you can't exactly downloading a shirt and wear it. 

and mos tof the "artists" that bitch about their music being downloaded don't really care about the music, just money...the way i see it, is if your material is being downloaded and you are getting more fans, then that should be cool. that's why i think Cold are being some pussies, according to JJO's website they're quitting because of poor record sales from their last album, which is lame. you all know i listen to quite a few not-so-much liked bands, and many of them have been kickin it for more then 10 years, they aren't letting not being super rich stop them from doing what they love.
